    <p>
        <h1>Definitions</h1>
    </p>


    <p>Next we show the definition of the different types of glasses:</p>

    <dl>
        <dt><b>Glasses to correct the eyesight:</b></dt>
        <dd>
            Set of two glasses with optical graduation, placed in a frame that rests on the nose <br> and that is held behind the ears with sideburns, with object to correct a visual <br> defect.
        </dd>

        <dt><b>Sunglasses:</b></dt>
        <dd>
            They are colored or darkened glasses that are intented to protect the eyes from <br> direct and annoying light.
        </dd>

        <dt><b>Protective glasses:</b></dt>
        <dd>
            They are a type of glasses used to prevent the entry of objects, water or chemicals <br> in the eyes.
        </dd>
    </dl>

